headline: How The Narrative Around Hasbro HAS Is Shifting With New Targets And Licensing Deals
summary: Why Hasbro’s Fair Value Model Just Got a Subtle Upgrade Analysts recently nudged their modeled fair value for Hasbro to $96.23 from $93.54, paired with a small adjustment to the discount rate to 7.68% from 7.70% and a revenue growth assumption of 5.51% from 5.35%. These shifts line up with fresh research calls that have lifted price targets by about $9 to $10 and, in some cases, taken views closer to the high $90s, reflecting updated thinking around how Hasbro’s revenue story could play out...
